OL,3,CMeet the Archdeacon of Carlisle as
OL,4,CChurch of England faces recruitment
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"I did my best and it is still here, I
OL,8,Fcan't have done any disasters.
OL,10,FSpeaking about her new position as an
OL,11,Farchdeacon, she said: "I am a bridge
OL,12,Fbetween the diocese and the parish.
OL,14,F"So I talk to the parishes about what
OL,15,Fthe diocese is saying and what they
OL,16,Fhave to offer. I then go back to the
OL,17,Fdiocese centrally and say what the
OL,18,Fparish and clergy are saying."
